Will ya !

257
00:21:08,050 --> 00:21:10,720
But, all in all,
It served me pretty well.

258
00:21:10,720 --> 00:21:14,720
Get inside, will ya ?
I didn't mean
To offend you, fergus.

259
00:21:20,060 --> 00:21:22,430
Fergus.

260
00:21:22,430 --> 00:21:25,170
Yeah ? I'm sorry.

261
00:21:25,170 --> 00:21:29,170
I- I know that
Wasn't very easy for you.

262
00:21:29,780 --> 00:21:33,780
The pleasure was all mine. 

263
00:21:38,020 --> 00:21:40,650
Oh, no, it was mine.

264
00:21:40,650 --> 00:21:44,660
Believe me,
It was my pleasure.

265
00:21:47,460 --> 00:21:50,160
What the fuck is this ?
Nothin', man.

266
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:52,930
He just took me out
For a pee.

267
00:21:52,930 --> 00:21:56,940
Put the fuckin' hood
On him.

268
00:22:03,280 --> 00:22:05,210
What the fuck is this ?
Nothin'.

269
00:22:05,210 --> 00:22:07,350
He's just got
A sense of humor,
That's all.

270
00:22:07,350 --> 00:22:10,490
When you're on duty
You'll keep your
Fuckin' mouth shut.

271
00:22:10,490 --> 00:22:14,490
Go on and get some sleep.
Yeah, get
Some sleep.

272
00:22:33,150 --> 00:22:36,950
Did he talk ?

273
00:22:36,950 --> 00:22:39,950
Didn't
Make you laugh ?

274
00:22:39,950 --> 00:22:42,520
Here, have
Some breakfast.

275
00:22:42,520 --> 00:22:44,460
Good morning,
Fergus.

276
00:22:44,460 --> 00:22:48,260
So, he knows your name ?
Yeah, I told him.

277
00:22:48,260 --> 00:22:51,730
Are you all there ?
Come here.

278
00:22:51,730 --> 00:22:54,640
I said come here !

279
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:58,640
Back in a minute,
Jody.

280
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:07,250
You'll have minimum contact with that prisoner !
Yeah, okay.

281
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:09,420
You know why ?
Why ?

282
00:23:09,420 --> 00:23:13,420
Because tomorrow we
Might have to shoot him,
That's why.

283
00:23:24,070 --> 00:23:28,070
They givin' you
Trouble, fergus ?

284
00:23:29,240 --> 00:23:30,980
It happens.

285
00:23:30,980 --> 00:23:33,880
There's two kinds
Of people:

286
00:23:33,880 --> 00:23:37,880
Those who give
And those who take.

287
00:23:39,720 --> 00:23:43,730
Take off
The hood, man.

288
00:23:44,890 --> 00:23:48,900
It's okay.

289
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:51,530
I understand.

290
00:23:51,530 --> 00:23:55,540
Don't mind if
I prattle on, do you ?

291
00:23:57,070 --> 00:24:01,080
I take it by your silence
That you don't.

292
00:24:03,310 --> 00:24:06,120
Two types, fergus:

293
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:10,120
The scorpion
And the frog.

294
00:24:10,250 --> 00:24:13,990
Ever heard of 'em ?

295
00:24:13,990 --> 00:24:18,000
A scorpion wants
To cross the river,
But he can't swim.

296
00:24:19,060 --> 00:24:23,070
Goes to
A frog who can
And asks for a ride.

297
00:24:23,700 --> 00:24:27,610
Frog says,
"if I give you
A ride on my back,

298
00:24:27,610 --> 00:24:29,340
You'll go
And sting me."

299
00:24:29,340 --> 00:24:32,950
Scorpion replies,
"it would not be in
My interest to sting you...

300
00:24:32,950 --> 00:24:36,550
Since, as I'll
Be on your back,
We both would drown."

301
00:24:36,550 --> 00:24:40,450
Frog thinks about
This logic for a while
And accepts the deal.

302
00:24:40,450 --> 00:24:44,460
Takes the scorpion
On his back,
Braves the waters,

303
00:24:45,190 --> 00:24:49,200
Halfway over
Feels a burning spear
In his side...

304
00:24:50,500 --> 00:24:54,500
And realizes the scorpion
Has stung him after all.

305
00:24:55,100 --> 00:24:59,110
And as they both
Sink beneath the waves,

306
00:24:59,880 --> 00:25:02,350
The frog cries out,

307
00:25:02,350 --> 00:25:06,020
"why'd you sting me
Mr. Scorpion ?

308
00:25:06,020 --> 00:25:10,020
For now
We both will drown."

309
00:25:11,090 --> 00:25:14,730
Scorpion replies,

310
00:25:14,730 --> 00:25:18,730
"I can't help it.
It's in my nature."

311
00:25:22,770 --> 00:25:25,970
So what's that
Supposed to mean ?

312
00:25:25,970 --> 00:25:28,910
Means what it says.

313
00:25:28,910 --> 00:25:32,910
A scorpion does
What is in its nature.

314
00:25:38,990 --> 00:25:41,520
Take off
The hood, man.

315
00:25:41,520 --> 00:25:45,530
Why ? 'Cause you're kind...

316
00:25:46,660 --> 00:25:50,660
And it's
In your nature.

317
00:26:07,050 --> 00:26:10,750
See ? I was right
About you.

318
00:26:10,750 --> 00:26:13,790
Don't be so sure.

319
00:26:13,790 --> 00:26:17,400
Jody's always right.

320
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:21,400
Where would you most
Like to be now, man ?

321
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:27,240
Doesn't matter where.
Come on, man.

322
00:26:27,970 --> 00:26:31,980
If this shit
Was all over.

323
00:26:33,110 --> 00:26:35,380
Uh,

324
00:26:35,380 --> 00:26:38,490
Havin' a pint
In the rock.

325
00:26:38,490 --> 00:26:41,360
You lack
Imagination, fergus.

326
00:26:41,360 --> 00:26:45,360
Think of something
More... Alluring.

327
00:26:45,790 --> 00:26:48,030
Like what ?

328
00:26:48,030 --> 00:26:52,030
Like... Havin' a pint
In the metro.

329
00:26:55,470 --> 00:26:59,440
Havin' two pints in the rock.
Havin' a pint
In the metro...

330
00:26:59,440 --> 00:27:02,110
And dil's
Havin' a margarita.

331
00:27:02,110 --> 00:27:05,250
Who's dil ?
Special friend.

332
00:27:05,250 --> 00:27:06,720
Oh, yeah.

333
00:27:06,720 --> 00:27:10,720
We got simple tastes, you and me.
Yup, the best.

334
00:27:13,320 --> 00:27:17,000
But you guys never
Get a break, do you ?

335
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:19,530
Do you ? Oh, yeah.

336
00:27:19,530 --> 00:27:23,240
We do a tour of duty
And we're finished.

337
00:27:23,240 --> 00:27:26,510
But you guys are
Never finished,
Are you ?

338
00:27:26,510 --> 00:27:30,510
We don't look on it
That way.

339
00:27:30,610 --> 00:27:32,980
Often wonder
How you do it.

340
00:27:32,980 --> 00:27:35,120
It depends
What you believe in.

341
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:38,790
What do you believe in ?
That you guys
Shouldn't be here.

342
00:27:38,790 --> 00:27:42,790
That simple ? Yup.

343
00:27:44,460 --> 00:27:47,600
Put that thing back on him, fergus.
He's hot !

344
00:27:47,600 --> 00:27:50,530
Doesn't matter if he's hot.
Just cover the fucker up.

345
00:27:50,530 --> 00:27:53,070
You got no feelings,
Woman !

346
00:27:53,070 --> 00:27:57,070
You shut your face !

347
00:27:57,570 --> 00:28:01,410
You're headed for trouble, fergus.
Okay, okay.

348
00:28:01,410 --> 00:28:05,080
He's a good soldier-

349
00:28:05,080 --> 00:28:09,090
I said
Shut the fuck up.

350
00:28:09,890 --> 00:28:13,890
He believes in the future.
Is that right ?

351
00:28:41,060 --> 00:28:43,930
Is it bad ?

352
00:28:43,930 --> 00:28:47,930
Not bad.

353
00:28:48,930 --> 00:28:52,940
Women are trouble. Do you know that, fergus ?
I didn't.

354
00:28:56,610 --> 00:28:59,710
Some kinds of women are.

355
00:28:59,710 --> 00:29:03,720
She can't help it.

356
00:29:05,350 --> 00:29:09,350
Dil, she was no trouble,
No trouble at all.

357
00:29:10,790 --> 00:29:14,790
- you liked her ?
- present tense, please, please.

358
00:29:18,330 --> 00:29:20,970
Love her...

359
00:29:20,970 --> 00:29:24,970
Wherever she is.

360
00:29:25,310 --> 00:29:29,310
I'm thinkin' of her now.
Would you think of her too ?

361
00:29:32,080 --> 00:29:34,380
I don't know her.

362
00:29:34,380 --> 00:29:38,390
- I want you
To do something for me.
- what ?

363
00:29:38,550 --> 00:29:42,560
- if they kill me-
- don't think that way.

364
00:29:43,090 --> 00:29:45,430
But they will,

365
00:29:45,430 --> 00:29:48,770
As sure
As night follows day.

366
00:29:48,770 --> 00:29:51,070
They have to.

367
00:29:51,070 --> 00:29:54,500
I want you
To find her out.

368
00:29:54,500 --> 00:29:57,710
Tell her
I was thinkin' of her.

369
00:29:57,710 --> 00:30:01,710
See if she's all right.
I don't know her.

370
00:30:03,050 --> 00:30:06,120
Take her picture. It's-

371
00:30:06,120 --> 00:30:10,120
Come here. It's in
My inside po-pocket.

372
00:30:15,160 --> 00:30:18,100
Take the whole lot.
I won't need it.

373
00:30:18,100 --> 00:30:22,100
I told you not
To talk that way.

374
00:30:22,370 --> 00:30:26,380
Go to millies hair salon
In spittalfields.

375
00:30:28,310 --> 00:30:31,310
Take her to the metro
For a margarita.

376
00:30:31,310 --> 00:30:33,850
You don't have
To tell her who you are.

377
00:30:33,850 --> 00:30:37,850
You just tell her jody was thinkin' of her-
Stop it.

378
00:30:54,670 --> 00:30:58,140
Volunteer ?

379
00:30:58,140 --> 00:31:02,150
We need you inside.

380
00:31:18,070 --> 00:31:19,970
We've heard word.

381
00:31:19,970 --> 00:31:23,970
They've used
Every trick in the book
And he's beginnin' to talk.

382
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:28,010
You're gonna have
To do it in the mornin'.

383
00:31:32,650 --> 00:31:34,950
You okay about that ?

384
00:31:34,950 --> 00:31:37,350
I'm a volunteer, am n't I ?
Good.

385
00:31:37,350 --> 00:31:40,920
Beginnin' to have
Me doubts about you
The past few days.

386
00:31:40,920 --> 00:31:43,060
Not the only one.

387
00:31:43,060 --> 00:31:47,060
Better get some sleep
Tonight, fergus.

388
00:31:48,670 --> 00:31:51,940
Peter. What ?

389
00:31:51,940 --> 00:31:54,470
Request permission to guard
The prisoner tonight.

390
00:31:54,470 --> 00:31:57,010
You're crazy. Don't let him, peter.
Shut the fuck up, jude.

391
00:31:57,010 --> 00:32:01,010
What do you want to do that for ?
It would make
Me feel better about it.

392
00:32:03,620 --> 00:32:07,620
Sure about that ?
Yeah, I'm sure.

393
00:32:08,620 --> 00:32:12,630
Okay. You're
A good man, fergus.

394
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:27,440
Don't.
I- I'm sorry.

395
00:32:33,180 --> 00:32:37,190
Help me.

396
00:32:37,720 --> 00:32:41,730
How can I ?
I don't know.

397
00:32:42,330 --> 00:32:46,330
I don't know.

398
00:32:46,560 --> 00:32:50,570
Just help me.

399
00:32:54,540 --> 00:32:58,540
Give me a cigarette.

400
00:33:13,930 --> 00:33:17,930
I don't even-
I don't even smoke.

401
00:33:18,930 --> 00:33:22,940
Thought it was
The right thing to do.

402
00:33:35,990 --> 00:33:39,990
Go to sleep now.
I don't want
To sleep.

403
00:33:41,060 --> 00:33:43,190
Tell me something.

404
00:33:43,190 --> 00:33:46,900
What ? A story.

405
00:33:46,900 --> 00:33:50,870
Like the one about the frog ?
And the scorpion ?

406
00:33:50,870 --> 00:33:54,240
No. No.

407
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:57,040
Tell me anything.

408
00:33:57,040 --> 00:34:01,050
"when I was a child,
Yeah ?

409
00:34:03,550 --> 00:34:07,560
"I thought as a child.

410
00:34:08,120 --> 00:34:11,020
"but when I became a man,

411
00:34:11,020 --> 00:34:15,030
I put away
Childish things."

412
00:34:16,500 --> 00:34:19,800
What does that mean ?

413
00:34:19,800 --> 00:34:22,600
Nothing.

414
00:34:22,600 --> 00:34:25,040
Nothing ?

415
00:34:25,040 --> 00:34:28,810
Tell me something.

416
00:34:28,810 --> 00:34:32,820
Anything.

417
00:34:36,190 --> 00:34:40,190
Not a lot of use,
Are you, fergus ?

418
00:34:44,400 --> 00:34:48,370
Me ?

419
00:34:48,370 --> 00:34:51,240
No.

420
00:34:51,240 --> 00:34:55,240
I'm not good for much.

421
00:35:23,310 --> 00:35:27,310
Come on, stand up.

422
00:35:28,450 --> 00:35:31,280
Turn to your right.

423
00:35:31,280 --> 00:35:35,290
Okay, step up.
One step.

424
00:35:36,190 --> 00:35:38,460
Okay, turn
To your right.

425
00:35:38,460 --> 00:35:42,460
Go forward.
Step up.

426
00:35:48,340 --> 00:35:52,340
Now to the left.

427
00:35:53,310 --> 00:35:57,310
I wish to say on behalf of the irish republican army-
Leave him be !

428
00:36:12,830 --> 00:36:16,300
Take the hood off,
Fergus.

429
00:36:16,300 --> 00:36:18,530
No.

430
00:36:18,530 --> 00:36:22,040
I want to see you
A bit, please. Please.

431
00:36:22,040 --> 00:36:26,040
Don't make me die
Like an animal.

432
00:36:38,220 --> 00:36:41,560
I'm glad
You're doin' it.

433
00:36:41,560 --> 00:36:43,830
Do you know that,
Fergus ?

434
00:36:43,830 --> 00:36:47,770
Why ?
'Cause you're
My friend.

435
00:36:47,770 --> 00:36:51,770
And I want you to go to the metro.
Stop that talk now !

436
00:36:54,340 --> 00:36:57,550
Hurling's a fast game, isn't it, fergus ?
The fastest.

437
00:36:57,550 --> 00:37:00,710
Faster than cricket ?
Cricket's in
The ha'penny place.

438
00:37:00,710 --> 00:37:04,720
So if I ran,
There's no way I could
Beat you, is there ?

439
00:37:04,790 --> 00:37:07,920
You won't run !
But if I did,

440
00:37:07,920 --> 00:37:11,930
You wouldn't shoot a brother in the back.
Jody !

441
00:37:13,500 --> 00:37:16,100
You stupid bastard !
What'd you say,
Faster ?

442
00:37:16,100 --> 00:37:19,500
I said you bastard ! Stop !
Gotta catch me first.

443
00:37:19,500 --> 00:37:23,510
Used to run the mile,
You know, four times
Around the cricket pitch.

444
00:37:24,040 --> 00:37:26,810
What was that game called ?
Hurling !

445
00:37:26,810 --> 00:37:29,350
What ? What ?
Hurling !

446
00:37:31,850 --> 00:37:35,850
Told you I was fast, huh ?

447
00:37:39,360 --> 00:37:43,360
Don't do it.

448
00:37:49,140 --> 00:37:53,140
Jody !

449
00:37:56,440 --> 00:38:00,450
All line up !
Follow me !

450
00:38:11,330 --> 00:38:14,060
Over here now !

451
00:38:14,060 --> 00:38:18,070
Jude !

452
00:38:50,340 --> 00:38:52,170
Fergus.

453
00:38:52,170 --> 00:38:56,180
You're back
On the bike, tommy ?

454
00:38:56,840 --> 00:38:58,810
How're ya keepin' ?
All right.

455
00:38:58,810 --> 00:39:02,820
And notice I've asked you nothin'.
That's wise, tommy.

456
00:39:04,220 --> 00:39:08,220
All right then.
I like bein' wise.

457
00:39:10,760 --> 00:39:14,130
So what do you need,
Fergus ?

458
00:39:14,130 --> 00:39:17,830
Need to go across the water.
Do ya now ?

459
00:39:17,830 --> 00:39:20,970
Need to lose myself
For a while.

460
00:39:20,970 --> 00:39:23,080
Aye.

461
00:39:23,080 --> 00:39:27,080
There's a man I know
Ships cattle to london.

462
00:40:58,950 --> 00:41:02,620
We're closing.

463
00:41:02,620 --> 00:41:04,120
You deaf ?

464
00:41:04,120 --> 00:41:07,120
I'll see you tomorrow, dil.
'Night.

465
00:41:07,120 --> 00:41:11,130
Want something in particular ?
Just a bit
Of a trim.

466
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:15,600
Come on.

467
00:41:30,480 --> 00:41:33,890
Someone recommended you ?
In a way.

468
00:41:33,890 --> 00:41:37,890
Who ? Uh- a guy I work with.

469
00:41:38,190 --> 00:41:42,200
What's his name ?
Does the water
Not get to your nails ?

470
00:41:42,530 --> 00:41:46,530
What's it to you ?
Nothing.

471
00:41:48,500 --> 00:41:50,570
You american ? No.

472
00:41:50,570 --> 00:41:53,440
You're not english.
No.

473
00:41:53,440 --> 00:41:56,540
Scottish ?
How'd you guess ?

474
00:41:56,540 --> 00:42:00,550
- the accent, I suppose.
- oh. What's it like ?

475
00:42:02,720 --> 00:42:06,720
Like treacle.

476
00:42:06,720 --> 00:42:10,730
Nice laugh.

477
00:42:17,570 --> 00:42:21,570
There. That should
Make her happy.

478
00:42:22,140 --> 00:42:26,150
Who's "she" ?
Don't know.
Who is "she" ?

479
00:43:01,280 --> 00:43:04,620
Hi, dil. Hiya, hon.

480
00:43:04,620 --> 00:43:08,630
 All right ?
 I suppose.

481
00:43:11,060 --> 00:43:15,030
Yes ? What'll it be ?
Bottle of guinness.

482
00:43:15,030 --> 00:43:19,040
Bottle of guinness.

483
00:43:19,770 --> 00:43:22,240
See that, col ?
See what, dil ?

484
00:43:22,240 --> 00:43:24,710
He gave me a look.
Did he ?

485
00:43:24,710 --> 00:43:27,410
I just cut his hair, you know.
Yeah ?

486
00:43:27,410 --> 00:43:31,420
So what do you think ?
Nice.

487
00:43:34,820 --> 00:43:36,490
There.
He did it again.

488
00:43:36,490 --> 00:43:40,500
I saw that one. That was a look.
What would you call that ?

489
00:43:42,130 --> 00:43:43,530
Ask him to ask me
What I'm drinking.

490
00:43:43,530 --> 00:43:47,540
- she wants to know do you want
To know what she's drinking.
- a margarita.

491
00:43:55,140 --> 00:43:59,150
Now he can look.

492
00:44:01,090 --> 00:44:04,250
Ask him does he
Like his hair, col.

493
00:44:04,250 --> 00:44:07,030
She wants to know, sir,
Do you like your hair.

494
00:44:07,030 --> 00:44:11,030
Tell her I'm very happy with it.
He's scottish, col.

495
00:44:11,360 --> 00:44:13,900
Scottish ? Yeah.

496
00:44:13,900 --> 00:44:17,140
What he say ?
He agreed
That he was.

497
00:44:17,140 --> 00:44:20,610
And what do you think
His name might be ?

498
00:44:20,610 --> 00:44:23,610
I have no thoughts
On the subject.

499
00:44:23,610 --> 00:44:25,680
Jimmy. Jimmy ?

500
00:44:25,680 --> 00:44:28,420
Jimmy. That's
What he said.

501
00:44:28,420 --> 00:44:30,950
Hiya, jimmy.

502
00:44:30,950 --> 00:44:34,960
Hi, dil.

503
00:44:36,260 --> 00:44:38,830
Sing us a song, dil.
Fuck off, dave.

504
00:44:38,830 --> 00:44:42,100
Come on, babe.
You know what
I like.

505
00:44:42,100 --> 00:44:46,100
Easy !

506
00:44:52,640 --> 00:44:55,550
Shit.
